n edition in 1966.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aHumanismzItaly. 0aHumanism. 0aRenaissancezItaly. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Italy.2bisacsh  aAlbertino Mussato.  aAlbizzi.  aAnnexation.  aBadia Fiorentina.  aBartolomeo Platina.  aBattle of Actium.  aBattle of Pharsalus.  aBattle of Zagonara.  aBenvenuto Rambaldi da Imola.  aBuonaccorso Pitti.  aBuonaccorso da Montemagno.  aCaesarism.  aCentral Italian.  aCity-state.  aClassicism.  aColuccio Salutati.  aCondottieri.  aCortona.  aCosimo de' Medici.  aCriticism.  aCulture of Italy.  aDonato Acciaioli.  aDuke of Florence.  aEinhard.  aEmbarrassment.  aEnglish Renaissance.  aEtruria.  aEuripides.  aFeudalism.  aFiesole.  aFilippo Brunelleschi.  aFilippo Villani.  aFinal Crisis.  aFrancesco Foscari.  aGaleazzo Visconti.  aGian Galeazzo Visconti.  aGiannozzo Manetti.  aGino Capponi.  aGiotto.  aGiovanni Morelli.  aGiovanni de' Medici (cardinal).  aGirolamo Savonarola.  aGothic art.  aGuarino da Verona.  aGuelphs and Ghibellines.  aHesiod.  aHistorical criticism.  aHouse of Visconti.  aHyperbole.  aHypocrisy.  aIrony.  aItalian Court.  aItalian Renaissance.  aItalian art.  aItalian grammar.  aItalian literature.  aItalian nationalism.  aItalian unification.  aItalians.  aKingdom of Italy.  aLatins (Italic tribe).  aLaudatio florentinae urbis.  aLeonardo Bruni.  aLiterature.  aLorenzo de' Medici.  aMatteo Palmieri.  aNiccolò Machiavelli.  aNorthern Italy.  aOn War.  aPadua.  aPamphlet.  aPanegyric.  aPapal States.  aPasquale Villari.  aPatrician (ancient Rome).  aPatrician (post-Roman Europe).  aPetrarch.  aPrincipate.  aQuattrocento.  aRadicalism (historical).  aRapprochement.  aRenaissance art.  aRenaissance.